# Madaf environment template — copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and edit.
# No values in this file are production secrets; there IS no production
# Supabase project in this phase (local stack only).
#
# For a hosted STAGING deployment (Vercel + hosted Supabase), see
# docs/deployment/STAGING_DEPLOYMENT_M7C.md — it lists the exact Vercel env
# vars, the forbidden vars, and the Supabase/Vercel setup checklists (M7C).

# ── Canonical public app origin ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The canonical public origin the app is served from. Client-visible (no
# secret). REQUIRED on any hosted deployment (production AND preview): it is
# the origin used to build shareable tokenized customer links — shop,
# showcase, store-signup and team-invite (src/lib/public-url.ts, M8E.2). It
# must be the public URL, NOT the per-deploy Vercel preview host — a preview
# host is gated by Vercel Deployment Protection and would bounce recipients to
# the Vercel login. Also a hint for the deployment safety linter + Supabase
# Auth Site/Redirect URLs. Leave blank locally (localhost is used as a safe
# fallback). Staging value:
#NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://madaf-drab.vercel.app

# ── Data mode ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# "mock" (default): UI reads from src/lib/mock/* — no backend, no auth.
# "supabase" (LOCAL DEV ONLY): the UI runs on the seeded local database
#   with REAL Supabase Auth (M4A). Supplier users sign in at /login;
#   /admin requires a session + tenant membership; reads run under RLS and
#   writes go through authenticated, tenant-validated RPCs. Customers order
#   via private tokenized links at /shop/<token> (no login). Owner/admin
#   manage the tenant team at /admin/team via tokenized email invitations
#   (/invite/<token>) (M4B). A user may belong to several tenants and switch
#   between them from the admin top bar (M4C). Order writes (M3A) and catalog
#   writes (M3B) are real. `supabase db reset` restores the clean demo data;
#   run supabase/bootstrap-auth.sql once after a reset to create the demo
#   auth users (see docs/AUTH_AND_ACCESS_MODEL.md).
# Anything other than exactly "supabase" means mock.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MADAF_DATA_MODE=mock

# ── Local Supabase (see supabase/README.md) ──────────────────────────────
# Values are printed by `supabase start` / `supabase status`. The
# publishable (anon) key below is the CLI's shared LOCAL default — fine to
# commit, useless outside your machine. In supabase mode this anon key is
# the REAL client credential: the browser and server auth clients use it,
# and the logged-in user's session (httpOnly cookies) scopes every request
# under RLS. The URL must be LOCAL (127.0.0.1/localhost).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:55321
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_ACJWlzQHlZjBrEguHvfOxg_3BJgxAaH

# Server-only — BYPASSES Row Level Security; never reaches the browser.
# Since M4A the app's read/write DATA path runs through the authenticated,
# cookie-bound client (not the service role). This key is used by LOCAL
# bootstrap/seed tooling AND, since M5B.1, as the TRUSTED server-only client
# that uploads/signs stored document PDFs (the `documents` bucket has no
# authenticated policies, so only the service role can write there — after
# the route authorizes the request). Set it in supabase mode to enable
# document PDF storage/download; leave blank in mock mode. Server-only,
# fail-closed (refuses production + non-local URLs); never NEXT_PUBLIC.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ── Trusted document-PDF storage (M5C) ───────────────────────────────────
# The `documents` bucket is server-trusted only (no authenticated storage
# policies). The dedicated trusted client
# (src/lib/data/trusted-document-storage.ts) is LOCAL-ONLY by default and
# FAILS CLOSED (refuses production NODE_ENV and non-local URLs); if it is
# unavailable the document route safely streams the PDF without storing it.
#
# To enable STORED PDFs in a hosted/production environment (opt-in), set:
#   MADAF_TRUSTED_DOCUMENT_STORAGE=enabled
#   MADAF_TRUSTED_DOCUMENT_STORAGE_PROJECT_REF=<your-project-ref>   # ALWAYS
#     required whenever storage is =enabled (the M7C safety linter errors if it
#     is missing/blank). Pins the URL to <ref>.supabase.co so it can't point at
#     another project.
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<server-only key>
# Default (unset) = "local-only". NEVER commit real keys; server-only vars,
# never NEXT_PUBLIC, never in the browser. Do NOT enable against a project
# you don't fully control.
#MADAF_TRUSTED_DOCUMENT_STORAGE=local-only
#MADAF_TRUSTED_DOCUMENT_STORAGE_PROJECT_REF=

# Optional: tenant the local-dev service/bootstrap tooling targets
# (defaults to the seeded demo tenant).
#MADAF_SUPABASE_TENANT_ID=11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111

# ── Auth method (M7B — phone OTP primary) ────────────────────────────────
# Madaf's primary supplier/admin sign-in is PHONE-NUMBER OTP. Email+password
# remains a secondary fallback (the seeded demo users are email-based) and is
# hidden in production unless email is the primary method. Server-only; never
# NEXT_PUBLIC. Whichever method is used, Supabase Auth issues a session bound
# to an auth.users id and tenant membership / RLS are unchanged.
#
# Hosted phone OTP REQUIRES an SMS provider configured in the Supabase
# dashboard (or a Send SMS Hook) — see docs/AUTH_AND_ACCESS_MODEL.md. NEVER
# commit Twilio/provider secrets to this repo; they live in Supabase secrets.
# LOCAL phone OTP is wired for you: supabase/config.toml enables a DUMMY,
# non-secret local SMS provider + [auth.sms.test_otp] so the test numbers
# below verify with code 123456 WITHOUT sending any real SMS (M7B.1).
#MADAF_AUTH_PRIMARY_METHOD=phone         # phone | email (default: phone)

# Server-enforced email/password policy (M7B.1). Email+password sign-in AND
# sign-up are ALLOWED when: email is the primary method, OR this flag is
# "true", OR NODE_ENV is not production (dev/local). So a phone-primary
# PRODUCTION deployment has email/password OFF at BOTH the UI and the server
# actions unless you explicitly opt in here. Enable it for an email-invite-
# heavy phone-primary deployment (see the invite limitation in the docs).
# Server-only; never NEXT_PUBLIC; missing/blank = false.
#MADAF_EMAIL_AUTH_ENABLED=false

# ── DEV / MOCK fake phone-OTP testing path (M7B) ─────────────────────────
# ⚠️ LOCAL/DEV TESTING ONLY. A side path to sign in with a FAKE number + FAKE
# code WITHOUT sending SMS, for experiments. Fail-closed and DISABLED by
# default. It is consulted ONLY in mock mode (no backend); in Supabase mode
# the app always uses real signInWithOtp/verifyOtp. It is HARD-DISABLED when
# NODE_ENV=production and against any non-local Supabase URL, so it can NEVER
# be a production bypass, and it grants no tenant access / never weakens RLS.
# For LOCAL SUPABASE-mode phone testing, use supabase/config.toml
# [auth.sms.test_otp] instead (real local session, RLS intact).
#
# The code is SERVER-ONLY — it is read only in the server action and is NEVER
# NEXT_PUBLIC / never shipped to the browser. Do NOT use real phone numbers.
#MADAF_DEV_PHONE_OTP_ENABLED=false
#MADAF_DEV_PHONE_OTP_ALLOWED_NUMBERS=+972500000001,+972500000002
#MADAF_DEV_PHONE_OTP_CODE=123456

# ── Legal invoicing (M6B–M6E — SANDBOX at most; NO real issuing exists) ────
# Read by src/lib/config/legal-invoicing.ts (server-only). Since M6E these
# three flags + the service-role-only DB kill switch (legal_numbering_settings,
# default off) + owner/admin + tenant readiness gate a DORMANT sandbox-only
# orchestration that, even fully enabled, writes ONLY clearly non-legal
# (sandbox=true, legal_effective=false) rows — a HARD CHECK makes a legally-
# effective row impossible. They do NOT issue anything real: no tax invoice,
# allocation number, provider/tax-authority call, payment, or PDF. See
# docs/LEGAL_INVOICING_ARCHITECTURE.md. (Historically M6B added only tax
# settings + an INERT legal schema — see
# docs/LEGAL_INVOICING_ARCHITECTURE.md). Turning them on changes NOTHING in
# M6B except the read-only status shown on /admin/settings/tax. ALL default
# OFF / disabled; a missing/blank value = OFF; legal issuing must FAIL CLOSED
# and is never enabled in mock/demo. Server-only; NEVER NEXT_PUBLIC. In M6B
# `MADAF_TAX_PROVIDER_MODE=production` is intentionally clamped to `disabled`
# (no certified provider integration exists). Do NOT turn these on for
# production: Madaf is not a legal tax invoice issuer and needs a
# tax/accounting/legal review + official-source verification (M6G) first.
#MADAF_LEGAL_INVOICING_ENABLED=false
# M6D: selects the legal-invoice provider adapter (server-only). `disabled` →
# NullProvider (unavailable); `sandbox` → SandboxProvider, a DETERMINISTIC MOCK
# that issues NOTHING and marks every response non-legal (no network, no real
# tax authority / SHAAM, no allocation number, no credentials). `production` is
# clamped to `disabled` (no real integration exists). The adapter is dormant —
# no route/UI calls it. Never NEXT_PUBLIC.
#MADAF_TAX_PROVIDER_MODE=disabled          # disabled | sandbox (production clamped off)
# M6C: gates the DORMANT app helper (src/lib/data/legal-numbering.ts, wired to
# nothing). Even =true issues NOTHING and draws no number unless the separate,
# service-role-only DB kill switch (legal_numbering_settings.enabled, default
# false) is also on — which nothing in M6C turns on. Internal preview only.
#MADAF_LEGAL_NUMBERING_ENABLED=false
